The paper discusses the application of graph colouring to biological networks, specifically protein-protein interaction (PPI) networks. This suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of computer science that deal with network analysis, such as cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of a well-known complete graph colouring algorithm, DSATUR, which falls under the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also explores the significance of node colouring information in identifying protein complexes, which may fall under the sub-category of q-bio.MN (Molecular Networks) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
